#include "killerkeys.dtsi"

/ {
    chosen {
        zmk,kscan = &kscan0;
    };
};
```

---

**What this does:** Both files are identical for now — they simply include the shared `.dtsi` file you just made. Since your left and right halves are mirrored (same pins, flipped PCB), they use the exact same matrix definition.

If the halves ever had *different* pin wiring you'd put the differences here, but in your case the shared `.dtsi` covers everything.

---

Your shield folder should now look like this:
```
boards/shields/killerkeys/
├── Kconfig.shield
├── Kconfig.defconfig
├── killerkeys.dtsi
├── killerkeys_left.overlay
└── killerkeys_right.overlay